      prompt: `<table style="border-collapse:collapse;margin:6px auto"><tr><th style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px"><em>x</em></th><th style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px"><em>y</em></th></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px;text-align:center">0</td><td style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px;text-align:center">22</td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px;text-align:center">1</td><td style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px;text-align:center">23</td></tr><tr><td style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px;text-align:center">2</td><td style="border:1px solid var(--border);padding:3px 12px;text-align:center">24</td></tr></table>The table shows three values of <em>x</em> and their corresponding values of <em>y</em>. There is a linear relationship between <em>x</em> and <em>y</em>. Which of the following equations represents this relationship?`,
